Outputs expose values from your Terraform configuration so they can be used by other modules, other Terraform states, or displayed after apply.

Defining outputs:
```hcl
output "data_lake_bucket_arn" {
  description = "ARN of the S3 data lake bucket"
  value       = aws_s3_bucket.data_lake.arn
}

output "rds_endpoint" {
  description = "Connection endpoint for the metadata database"
  value       = aws_db_instance.metadata.endpoint
  sensitive   = true  # hides value in CLI output and logs
}
```

Accessing outputs:
```bash
terraform output                        # show all outputs
terraform output data_lake_bucket_arn  # show one output
terraform output -json                  # machine-readable JSON
```

Cross-module usage:
```hcl
module "networking" {
  source = "./modules/vpc"
}

resource "aws_db_instance" "metadata" {
  db_subnet_group_name = module.networking.db_subnet_group_name
}
```

Remote state data source (cross-state sharing):
```hcl
data "terraform_remote_state" "network" {
  backend = "s3"
  config = {
    bucket = "my-terraform-state"
    key    = "network/terraform.tfstate"
    region = "us-east-1"
  }
}
```

DE use case: output the Redshift endpoint so your dbt profiles.yml can reference it.
